Consider the metric space (X,d), where $X=\{1,2,3,4\}$ and the metric $d:X\times X \rightarrow \mathbb{R}$ is given by:

\begin{equation*}
    d(x,y) =
    \begin{cases}
      0 & \text{if}\ x = y \\
      1 & \text{if}\ x \neq y
    \end{cases}
\end{equation*}

Determine whether the sequence $(x_n)_{n\geq 1}$ defined by $x_n = n$ converges to any point $x\in X$ with respect to the metric $d$.
